"v.模棱两可地说，支吾其词，说谎 【英】 v. 模棱两可地说，支吾 其词, 说谎(to use equivocal terms in order to deceive, mislead, hedge) 【考】 fawn : imperiousness / equivocate : directness(奉承的人不会傲慢/ 含糊其词的人不会直 截了当)equivocate : commitment / procrastinate : action(含糊其词是不想承诺 /拖延是不想行动)grandstand : impress / equivocate : deceive(哗众取宠是为了留下 印象/含糊其词是为了 欺骗) 【考】 equivocation : misleading / bromide : hackneyed(模棱两可的话特点是 误导的/庸俗之言特点 是陈腐的) 【同】 派生词: equivocation (n.模棱两可的话) 【例】 Don't equivocate! Just tell me the truth. v. 模棱两可他说(故意使用模棱两可的语言, 避免作明确的声明) 【记】equi平等, voc声音－声音差不多－含糊其词 【参】equivocal(adj 模棱两可的) = ambiguous = misleading = vague 【类】fawn: imperiousness = equivocate: directness奉承的不会傲慢 = 含糊其词的不会直截了当equivocate: commitment = procrastinate: action含糊其词是不想承诺 = 拖延是不想行动grandstand: impress = equivocate: deceive哗众取宠是为了留下印象 = 含糊其词是为了欺骗ambiguous: understand = equivocal: meaning模糊的缺乏理解 = 摸棱两可的缺乏含义 【反】communicate straightforwardly(直截了当地交流); waffle(v 胡扯)－speak unequivocally(说话不搪塞) 【记】equi + voice 相同的声音 【相关】vocation 召唤, 号召,天职,才能, 职业， avocation 副业, 业余爱好，convocation 集会, 召集，equivocate 说模棱两可的话, 支吾，evocation 唤出, 唤起, 招魂，invocation 祈祷, 符咒，provocation 激怒, 刺激, 挑衅，revocation 撤回，vocal 声音的 equivocate (v.)  early 15c., equivocaten, from Medieval Latin equivocatus, past participle of equivocare ""to call by the same name,"" from Late Latin aequivocus (see equivocation). Related: Equivocated; equivocating."
